\section{Part 1: Negative Numbers and Integer Operations}

\subsection{Negative Numbers: Addition and Subtraction}


\[
7+12=19
\]
\textbf{Same sign} (both $+$), we \textbf{add} numbers.

\[
-7-12=-19
\]
\textbf{Same sign} (both $-$), we \textbf{add} numbers ($7+12=19$). Final value is \textbf{negative} since both numbers are negative.

\[
-12+7=-5
\]
\textbf{Different sign} ($+$ and $-$), we \textbf{subtract} the smaller number from the bigger number ($12-7=5$). Final value is \textbf{negative} since negative $12$ is numerically larger than positive $7$.

\[
-7+12=5
\]
\textbf{Different sign} ($+$ and $-$), we \textbf{subtract} the smaller number from the bigger number. Final value is \textbf{positive} since positive $12$ is numerically larger than negative $7$.
